&gt; &gt; If you have a sword with a serial number stamped on it (on the
&gt; blade) then you have a mass produced so-called &quot;factory made&quot; sword.
&gt; Sometimes you will find some numbers stamped on the nakago (tang) of a
&gt; sword, usually two or three digits, which in that case might relate to
&gt; &quot;assembly&quot; numbers; these same numbers are often repeated on seppa,
&gt; tsuba, etc. Swords were &quot;registered&quot; after the war and continue to be
&gt; so today, but the Japanese government never required anything
&gt; (registration numbers) to be stamped on swords.
